ed Performance and Security\nThe Intel Core Ultra 7 includes advanced features, such as Intel Thread Director and Intel Turbo Boost Technology 2.0, optimising performance and enhancing responsiveness. It also supports Intel vPro Enterprise for enhanced security and manageability.\nSeamless Compatibility and Expandability\nThe Intel Core Ultra 7 is compatible with the LGA1851 socket and supports up to 256GB of DDR5 memory with speeds up to 6400 MT/s. Featuring PCI Express 5.0 and 4.0 support, connect high-speed graphics cards, storage devices, and other peripherals with ease. Upgrade to the Intel Core Ultra 7 and experience the pinnacle of desktop computing.\nFEATURES:\n\nExperience superior multitasking: Featuring 20 cores and 20 threads for seamless performance across applications.\nBoost performance when it matters: Achieving speeds up to 5.30GHz with Intel Turbo Boost Max Technology 3.0.\nEnjoy crisp, detailed visuals: Integrated Intel Graphics delivers a dynamic frequency of up to 1.95GHz.\nAccelerate AI processing: Benefit from the dedicated Intel AI Boost NPU for faster AI tasks.\nSupports high-speed memory: Compatible with up to DDR5 6400 MT/s for responsive computing.\nConnect multiple displays: Supporting up to 4 displays for enhanced productivity and immersive experiences.\nTake advantage of advanced security features: Intel vPro Enterprise provides comprehensive security and manageability.\nCreate content faster: Hardware encode/decode support for H.264, H.265 (HEVC), AV1, and VP9 codecs.\nExperience faster data transfer: Supports PCI Express 5.0 and 4.0 for high-speed peripherals.\n\nSPECIFICATIONS:\n\nEssentials:\n\nProduct Collection: IntelÂ® Coreâ„˘ Ultra Processors (Series 2)\nCode Name: Products formerly Arrow Lake\nVertical Segment: Desktop\nProcessor Number: 265\n\n\nCPU Specifications:\n\nTotal Cores: 20\n# of Performance-cores: 8\n# of Efficient-cores: 12\n# of Low Power Efficient-cores: 0\nTotal Threads: 20\nMax Turbo Frequency: 5.30GHz\nIntelÂ