˘, WindowsML, DirectML, ONNX RT, WebNN\n\n\nAdvanced Features:\n\nIntelÂ® Gaussian & Neural Accelerator: 3.5\nIntelÂ® Thread Director: Yes\nIntelÂ® Speed Shift Technology: Yes\nIntelÂ® Turbo Boost Max Technology 3.0: Yes\nIntelÂ® Turbo Boost Technology: 2.0\nIntelÂ® Hyper-Threading Technology: No\nIntelÂ® 64: Yes\nInstruction Set: 64-bit\nInstruction Set Extensions: IntelÂ® SSE4.1, IntelÂ® SSE4.2, IntelÂ® AVX2\nIdle States: Yes\nEnhanced Intel SpeedStepÂ® Technology: Yes\nThermal Monitoring Technologies: Yes\nIntelÂ® Volume Management Device (VMD): Yes\n\n\nSecurity & Reliability\n\nIntel vProÂ® Eligibility: Intel vProÂ® Enterprise\nIntelÂ® Threat Detection Technology (TDT): Yes\nIntelÂ® Active Management Technology (AMT): Yes\nIntelÂ® Standard Manageability (ISM): Yes\nIntelÂ® Remote Platform Erase (RPE): Yes\nIntelÂ® One-Click Recovery: Yes\nIntelÂ® Secure Key: Yes\nIntelÂ® Control-Flow Enforcement Technology: Yes\nIntelÂ® Total Memory Encryption - Multi Key: Yes\nIntelÂ® AES New Instructions: Yes\nIntelÂ® Trusted Execution Technology: Yes\nExecute Disable Bit: Yes\nIntelÂ® OS Guard: Yes\nIntelÂ® Boot Guard: Yes\nMode-based Execute Control (MBEC): Yes\nIntelÂ® Stable IT Platform Program (SIPP): Yes\nIntelÂ® Virtualization Technology with Redirect Protection (VT-rp): Yes\nIntelÂ® Virtualization Technology (VT-x): Yes\nIntelÂ® Virtualization Technology for Directed I/O (VT-d): Yes\nIntelÂ® VT-x with Extended Page Tables (EPT): Yes\n\n\n\nWHATâ€™S IN THE BOX:\n\nIntelÂ® Coreâ„˘ Ultra 7 265 LGA1851 2.40GHz 20-Core CPU x1\n\nWhy Intel?\nFor decades, Intel has powered the world\'s most innovative devices and solutions. From desktops to laptops, Intel desktop processors deliver the performance and reliability that users demand. Choosing an Intel processor means investing in a future-proof platform backed by cutting-edge technology and unparalleled support. Experience the difference with Intel.\n',8066.34,'https://www.syntech.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BX80768265_IntelÂ®-Core-Ultra-7-265-LGA1851-2.40GHz-20-Core-CPU_wr_01a.jpg','Components, CPU, Intel CPU',0,1,1,'2025-12-11 01:57:14.409','2025-12-11 04:55:36.711','New',0,NULL,NULL),('fd57c3eb-1a39-436f-93ca-b9ec5c217874','BX8071514900K','Intel 14th Gen Core i9-14900K LGA1700 3.2GHz 24-Core CPU','With an increase in core count, Intel 14th Gen processors continue to utilize Intelâ€™s performance hybrid architecture to optimize your gaming, content creation, and productivity. Leverage industry-first bandwidth of up to 16 PCIe 5.0 lanes and DDR5 memory up to 5600 MT/s. Supercharge your CPU performance with a powerful suite of tuning and overclocking tools. Enjoy your favourite experiences in up to 4 simultaneous 4K@60Hz displays or up to 8K@60Hz HDR Video with dynamic noise suppression. Support for the IntelÂ® 700 series chipsets and backwards compatibility with the IntelÂ® 600 series chipsets allow you to access the features you need for any task. Whether you are working, streaming, gaming, or creating, the 14th Gen IntelÂ® Coreâ„˘ desktop processors deliver the next generation of breakthrough performance.\nThe 14th Gen IntelÂ® Coreâ„˘ desktop processors deliver the next generation of breakthrough core performance. IntelÂ® Turbo Boost Max Technology 3.0 further strengthens lightly threaded performance by identifying the best-performing performance cores. Meanwhile, additional E-cores enable an increase in IntelÂ® Smart Cache (L3) for more efficient processing of larger data sets and better performance. The P-core and E-core L2 cache has also increased compared to the previous generation of IntelÂ® processors, minimizing the amount of time spent swapping data between cache and memory to speed up your workflow. Unleash the power of next-level performance with the 14th Gen IntelÂ® Coreâ„˘ desktop processor advantage.\nFEATURES:\n\n24 Cores\n32 Threads\nMax Turbo Frequency of up to 6.0GHz\n36MB IntelÂ® Smart Cache\nSupport for DDR4 and DDR5 memory\nBuilt for serious gaming\nBest overclocking experience\nSmart solutions for enthusiasts and creators\n\nSPECIFICATIONS:\n\nEssentials:\nProduct Collection: 14th Generation IntelÂ® Coreâ„˘ i9 Processors\nCode Name: Products formerly Raptor Lake\nVertical Segment: Desktop\nProcessor Number: i9-14900K\nCPU Specifications:\nTotal Cores: 24\n# of Performance-cores: 8\n# of Efficient-cores: 16\nTotal Threads: 32\nMax Turbo Frequency: 6.0GHz\nIntelÂ® Thermal Velocity Boost Frequency: 6.0GHz\nIntelÂ® Turbo Boost Max Technology 3.0 Frequency: 5.8GHz\nPerformance-core Max Turbo Frequency: 5.6GHz\nEfficient-core Max Turbo Frequency: 4.4GHz\nPerformance-core Base Frequency: 3.2GHz\nEfficient-core Base Frequency: 2.4GHz\nCache: 36 MB IntelÂ® Smart Cache\nTotal L2 Cache: 32 MB\nProcessor Base Power: 125 W\nMaximum Turbo Power: 253 W\nMemory Specifications:\nMax Memory Size (dependent on memory type): 192 GB\nMemory Types:Â Up to DDR5 5600 MT/s, Up to DDR4 3200 MT/s\nMax # of Memory Channels: 2\nMax Memory Bandwidth: 89.6 GB/s\nProcessor Graphics:\nProcessor Graphics: IntelÂ® UHD Graphics 770\nGraphics Base Frequency: 300MHz\nGraphics Max Dynamic Frequency: 1.65GHz\nGraphics Output: eDP 1.4b, DP 1.4a, HDMI 2.1\nExecution Units: 32\nMax Resolution (HDMI): 4096 x 2160 @ 60Hz\nMax Resolution (DP): 7680 x 4320 @ 60Hz\nMax Resolution (eDP â€“ Integrated Flat Panel): 5120 x 3200 @ 120Hz\nDirectX* Support: 12\nOpenGL* Support: 4.5\nOpenCL* Support: 3.0\nMulti-Format Codec Engines: 2\nIntelÂ® Quick Sync Video: Yes\nIntelÂ® Clear Video HD Technology: Yes\n# of Displays Supported: 4\nExpansion Options:\nDirect Media Interface (DMI) Revision: 4.0\nMax # of DMI Lanes: 8\nScalability: 1S Only\nPCI Express Revision: 5.0 and 4.0\nPCI Express Configurations: Up to 1Ă—16+4, 2Ă—8+4\nMax # of PCI Express Lanes: 20\nAdvanced Features:\nIntelÂ® Gaussian & Neural Accelerator: 3.0\nIntelÂ® Thread Director: Yes\nIntelÂ® Deep Learning Boost (IntelÂ® DL Boost): Yes\nIntelÂ® Speed Shift Technology: Yes\nIntelÂ® Thermal Velocity Boost: Yes\nIn